There were 322 new cases of coronavirus infection in South Korea between 00:00 and 4:00 p.m. on March 5, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 6088, bringing the total number of deaths to 40 and curing 88 cases. It was the first time in 45 days that the number of cases in South Korea has exceeded 6,000.

According to the South Korean Foreign Ministry News 5, as of 3:00 pm that day, because of the new pneumonia epidemic in South Korea to take immigration control measures have increased to 98 countries and regions.

Of the 5,766 cases confirmed as of midnight, 4,327 were in Taegu and 861 in North Gyeongsang Province, representing 75% and 14.9% , respectively. On average, 177.6 and 32.3 out of 100,000 people were diagnosed in both places, with 0.3 to 4.1 in the rest of the country and 11.1 across the country.

Outside Taegu and Gyeongbuk, the country has 110 confirmed cases in Gyeonggi Province, 103 in Seoul, 92 in Busan, 86 in South Chungcheong Province and 74 in South Gyeongsang Province.

As of midnight on the 5th, 69.4% of the 5,766 confirmed cases in South Korea were related to group infection. The total number of confirmed cases associated with Xintiandi church was 3,452(59.9%) , with the majority coming from Taegu (3,013) and Qingbei (348) .

According to a report by Yonhap News Agency, the first overall coordinator of the Central Disaster Safety Department, Kim gang-ri, said on the 5th that the testing of symptomatic believers in Xintiandi in the Taegu region was over, tests are now being carried out on asymptomatic believers and other citizens, and it can be predicted that the number of confirmed cases will gradually decrease.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Korea, the number of newly confirmed cases per day (from 0000 on the previous day to 0000 on the same day) has declined for four consecutive days. Source: Korea Central Epidemic Prevention Department

Although the number of confirmed cases is on the rise, there is no centralized area with confirmed cases except Daegu and the city of Gyeongsang, North Gyeongsang Province, which was designated as a special control area on the 5th, Jin said. But he cautioned that it would be a few days before the trend could be sustained.

South Korea's disease management headquarters also said Friday, north-east Gyeongbuk has again a collective infection, a sanatorium in Fenghua District County, 112 patients and staff, 36 confirmed infection.

The South Korean government has tested more than 2,300 of the more than 5,000 people with symptoms as of March 2 after it obtained a list of more than 9,300 Xintiandi believers in Taegu in February.

According to Yonhap News Agency reported that the government has since 11 am on the 5th, the New World Church headquarters launched an administrative investigation. Seoul also said on the 3rd that the city government found Xintiandi Legal Person "Harm Public Welfare" , decided to revoke Xintiandi legal person license, and will hold a hearing next week.

The Church of Xintiandi, at the center of the storm, donated 12 billion won (70.25 million yuan) that day to the social welfare fund-raiser, a fund-raiser to fight the epidemic, the Daegu branch and the Central Committee contributed 10 billion and 2 billion won respectively.

"Social Welfare common fund-raising meeting, " said the relevant people, did not get advance notice of Xintiandi, through media reports to know the donation news. This person said that when the donation amount is large, the two sides will usually discuss the use in advance, but Xintiandi did not go through this procedure, but directly through the fund-raising meeting public fund-raising account to complete the donation. The fund-raising meeting is the direction of the use of the funds are in-house discussions, will also consult with new heaven and earth.

The New World Church apologized again on the same day. The church expressed deep regret over the many confirmed cases in the church and said it would spare no efforts in organizing manpower and material resources to provide support. It looked forward to an early end of the epidemic and wished the patients a speedy recovery.
